        <p>You can add a shadow effect to an object in<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture"> an image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> a frame</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture"> or to the image itself</MadCap:conditionalText>. This helps to give your<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture"> image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> object</MadCap:conditionalText> the appearance of depth. When you create a shadow effect, you have control over where the shadow appears, how much shadow is shown, the color of the shadow, and the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">transparency</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">opacity</MadCap:conditionalText> of the shadow.</p>
